&lt;a href="http://www.zhihu.com/question/306642529?utm_campaign=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_source=rss&amp;utm_content=title" target="_blank"&gt;如何评价AQR的新书《20 for Twenty》，以及Quant该如何选择和学习AQR的论文来获益？&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
            
&lt;a href="http://www.zhihu.com/question/278289299?utm_campaign=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_source=rss&amp;utm_content=title" target="_blank"&gt;如何看待果仁网，聚宽等quant网站的收费培训？&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
            </description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">水心记</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 15 Feb 2022 12:07:43 +0800</pubDate><guid>http://www.zhihu.com/question/26108790/answer/2324177300</guid></item><item><title>什么是microprice？</title><link>http://www.zhihu.com/question/513782601/answer/2328043857?utm_campaign=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_source=rss&amp;utm_content=title</link><description>&lt;p data-pid="BkfUaiCw"&gt;好问题，结合最近读到的一篇Microprice Research，来梳理一下，抛砖引玉。注：实际生产中的microprice非常复杂，都会掺proprietary alpha，就是每个shop的ip了。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Prerequisite&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p data-pid="ccbmrnQR"&gt;在Orderbook的语境下，什么才是fair price呢？&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Mid-price?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic1.zhimg.com/v2-610169c44a41aad265d988aa97244871_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="142" data-rawheight="52" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-610169c44a41aad265d988aa97244871" data-watermark-src="" data-private-watermark-src="" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="_VZVss4y"&gt;Pa是best ask, Pb是best bid。看起来通俗易懂，但是有以下3点缺点:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li data-pid="ZU8RnZfi"&gt;Mid 高度自相关(auto-correlated)，这个现象也叫bid-ask-bounce&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-pid="uMsWt25F"&gt;Mid相比于quote来说，变化的频率低，因此是一个低频信号&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-pid="dw931d7d"&gt;Mid没有考虑volume&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Weighted Mid?&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-pid="9n1LUQqO"&gt;好，我们来加入Volume&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic4.zhimg.com/v2-230b46512625a7197c3d4e56b5b7b66b_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="149" data-rawheight="41" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-230b46512625a7197c3d4e56b5b7b66b" data-watermark-src="" data-private-watermark-src="" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic4.zhimg.com/v2-be93229ed267d1a8ba3dea138567424c_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="103" data-rawheight="51" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-be93229ed267d1a8ba3dea138567424c" data-watermark-src="" data-private-watermark-src="" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="Yi0nGZTi"&gt;这里的I也叫imbalance，这里的Qb是total volume at best bid, Qa是total volume at best ask, 分别也叫bid size和ask size。至此，我们已经有了现代Microprice研究的起点。Weighted Mid并不是完美的，它也有2点缺点:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li data-pid="6JoINSkv"&gt;因为每次imbalance的变化都会导致weighted mid的变化，因此它作为high frequency volatility estimation的时候非常noisy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-pid="EvvlauDV"&gt;因为weighted mid不是一个martingale，所以有一些反直觉的现象。比如Pb = 10, Qb = 9, Pa = 10.02, Qa = 27, 此时weighted mid是 9/(9+27) * 10.02 + (1-9/(9+27))  10 = 10.005，此时如果来了一个sell order 1@10.01，此时新的weighted mid 是 1/(1+9)  10.01 + (1- 1/(1+9)) * 10 = 10.009, 新来了卖单，应该让fair price降低，此时却上升了。&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;b&gt;Microprice&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;b&gt;定义&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-pid="z-4oRJ1L"&gt;掌声有请本文的主角，microprice，本文的microprice特指Stoikov, 2018提出的microprice，主要用的L1 orderbook，实际生活里有更多depth的。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-7decfaff95254f295a19ccab6249bf03_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="176" data-rawheight="43" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-7decfaff95254f295a19ccab6249bf03" data-watermark-src="" data-private-watermark-src="" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="6ukFZd4J"&gt;M是mid， I是老朋友imbalance，S是bid-ask spread。如何来estimate g呢？Stoikov认为，microprice是the limit of a sequence of expected mid-prices. 数学语言是:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic1.zhimg.com/v2-28bd3ccf534ac601d8205ed304fac437_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="626" data-rawheight="348" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-28bd3ccf534ac601d8205ed304fac437" data-watermark-src="v2-60e277af1d780c177c055a6e27a88ea8" data-private-watermark-src="v2-8e7776c536f543aa8f4c475c5edbeab7" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="DmOVHm-E"&gt;为什么要take the limit of expected mid as time goes to infinity呢？作者认为1) microprice是horizon independent的，这样trade at different frequencies的asset可以互相比较 2) mid里的microstructure noise被filter out了。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="kOD27eZZ"&gt;接着作者提出两个假设：&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li data-pid="wMWk1P2S"&gt;Orderbook中的信息由3-d Markov process Ft = sigma_field(M_t, I_t, St)产生的filtration决定。其中M_t是mid，S_t是bid-ask spread，I_t是top of book imbalance。这里作者指出可以加入Level2的信息。&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-pid="HRimrm2v"&gt;Expected mid price increments 独立于mid price level，即：&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-efdf28b88ed8850b31caa5faea453a83_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="532" data-rawheight="54" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-efdf28b88ed8850b31caa5faea453a83" data-watermark-src="" data-private-watermark-src="" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="LTSywUk-"&gt;   这样每个tick的price dynamics都相同。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="mrGIjC3v"&gt;由这两个假设，作者得出：&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic3.zhimg.com/v2-c1272913b5b88e3a7bd62dba2e3e671d_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="624" data-rawheight="333" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-c1272913b5b88e3a7bd62dba2e3e671d" data-watermark-src="v2-665c9646862885d7c8d2081464ba1ce2" data-private-watermark-src="v2-38017a5a7ce5ceeb514a706e96c7d6b7" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Finite state space example&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-pid="HoM-P0vp"&gt;为了能计算microprice， (Mt, I_t, St) 必须有explicit的dynamics。值得指出，如果I_t独立于M_t, microprice = midprice，而如果I_t是Brownian motion and behaves a particular way at the boundary, microprice = weighted mid. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="e2T4MUyi"&gt;让我们用discrete time step，那么It就从1&amp;lt;=i&amp;lt;=n中取离散值，S_t从1&amp;lt;=s&amp;lt;=m中取离散值。Imbalance的离散化就是:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic4.zhimg.com/v2-4a5c3c95130794c814688c9ed305fc65_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="276" data-rawheight="98" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-4a5c3c95130794c814688c9ed305fc65" data-watermark-src="v2-fe33fbb95df574d4d11a23d0c537ff24" data-private-watermark-src="v2-4bd443df8637f8783141b78ab3321dee" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="INp-Vj6K"&gt;Spread St可以用number of ticks表示。Midprice change Mt+1 - M_t从 K = [-0.01, -0.005, 0.005, 0.01]。这里用的half tick因为如果bid或者ask move by 1 cent, mid moves by 0.5 cent. 用x = (i,s) 来代表state space of Xt = (I_t, S_t).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic3.zhimg.com/v2-7174e6ca42b1748d67c57d2514d7fcbd_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="551" data-rawheight="539" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-7174e6ca42b1748d67c57d2514d7fcbd" data-watermark-src="v2-a66e900ad6cb908f3a63bcc8fc639238" data-private-watermark-src="v2-e50efa87ce4c2957f7df9f58840d02c3" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-e1f57fd14e1510aac818568f7cc91834_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="545" data-rawheight="110" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-e1f57fd14e1510aac818568f7cc91834" data-watermark-src="v2-58175ff538f0e8ea874f7e79f7a8b465" data-private-watermark-src="v2-5d9d9a826a87044c4f1cd15145bae5b0" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="xwMqYM8v"&gt;作者指出，以上计算microprice的方法是不guarantee convergence的。如果Q,R,T不被estimated carefully, 可能会incorporate drift in data，导致Pi blow up。因此引入以下条件来确保convergence。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic1.zhimg.com/v2-1449f8c6166863e5c21ed2cbca37c17d_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="556" data-rawheight="559" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-1449f8c6166863e5c21ed2cbca37c17d" data-watermark-src="v2-6ac780edf16cd92de56f0188d153798a" data-private-watermark-src="v2-4412e7e8c3b633adec6c716c8313fec0" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;实证研究&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-pid="ETjhCWEx"&gt;数据&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="f1ncs1f1"&gt;作者选用了Bank of America(BAC)和Chevron (CVX)两只股票的bid ask quote，注意到BAC和CVX有非常不同的微观结构，体现在不同的tick size分布上，BAC的mid也change much less frequency than CVX。这个区别，来源于BAC的price比CVX更低，tick size of 1 cent占price的百分比更高，因次BAC也叫large tick stock。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic3.zhimg.com/v2-e48000f9765cfb2576af16708a48eb5e_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="642" data-rawheight="260" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-e48000f9765cfb2576af16708a48eb5e" data-watermark-src="v2-4d69f74e06f9b25c697528ca4cea1819" data-private-watermark-src="v2-e01715932b55719a8c6d4b9bf061e2fb" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="8mUr7Cgy"&gt;实验set up&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic3.zhimg.com/v2-f112ffc279c891004ca7f04d1c4998c7_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="848" data-rawheight="475" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-f112ffc279c891004ca7f04d1c4998c7" data-watermark-src="v2-177ea55cf558822186f159cc6313214a" data-private-watermark-src="v2-bc371165354eb600a614166301d47faf" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="sEdujaxN"&gt;可以看到microprice adjustment在midprice和weighted mid之间:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic1.zhimg.com/v2-c240eac3d048baa1333af42e63afb96b_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="648" data-rawheight="276" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-c240eac3d048baa1333af42e63afb96b" data-watermark-src="v2-cc110027176d2ab874b42e5e1fa67d04" data-private-watermark-src="v2-5ee75103e3c5dc093bc9e1762056aa3f" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="npjN2X68"&gt;注意到当spread widen, slope of microprice as a function of imbalance lessen,也就是说imbalance are less informative. 另外，对于BAC这种large tick stock来说，microprice adjustment更大。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="Ydcpj7_L"&gt;因为microprice是horizon-independent的，因此用来评估预测future price的有效性，需要选一个timescale。如果time scale太小，那么empirical price change will suffer from microstructure noise, i.e. autocorrelation effects. 如果time scale太大，那么empirical price change就会有很多noise，95% 置信区间也会很大。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="rjBGQ0Ti"&gt;两个实验。&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic4.zhimg.com/v2-5df0f0f26cdf983e810e27b31aac2f2e_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="695" data-rawheight="380" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-5df0f0f26cdf983e810e27b31aac2f2e" data-watermark-src="v2-cb5b3999ee1697e6a4d75501458d6f63" data-private-watermark-src="v2-961e6143d38e75f6366fbb85ff709f53" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic1.zhimg.com/v2-07ed018aebd0d9dbe0ae0faa513235c5_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="694" data-rawheight="97" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-07ed018aebd0d9dbe0ae0faa513235c5" data-watermark-src="" data-private-watermark-src="" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic3.zhimg.com/v2-49245a559ec4ee02fafdf5209d104701_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="692" data-rawheight="782" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-49245a559ec4ee02fafdf5209d104701" data-watermark-src="v2-10f0051f9370f90262896e391825c44c" data-private-watermark-src="v2-6647770b8592337801acd64e4c0da2d4" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="RkX_IJ4f"&gt;结论:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic4.zhimg.com/v2-696d03979de729fbb97b9f21cff28fa8_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="707" data-rawheight="246" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-696d03979de729fbb97b9f21cff28fa8" data-watermark-src="v2-adff69cdd13031b26c5a6bc00f267778" data-private-watermark-src="v2-9e6176ca63abcc8a45c60b6f62efbbf2" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;代码实现&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-pid="V20jcGWL"&gt;(文末有原作者Github repo)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="K33iss_c"&gt;生成Orderbook statistics:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic2.zhimg.com/v2-c637a2c0a75f45e536bb5726b5e7d6c7_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="728" data-rawheight="289" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-c637a2c0a75f45e536bb5726b5e7d6c7" data-watermark-src="v2-ec2a37013a0a05cd65bf953ffa10b2ec" data-private-watermark-src="v2-14b817baf4d841089fa71bb3866b43cf" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="0wDsJn7W"&gt;Symmetrize data (to ensure convergence)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic1.zhimg.com/v2-7f760f222bc8c5ca81935411ddea0938_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="553" data-rawheight="541" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-7f760f222bc8c5ca81935411ddea0938" data-watermark-src="v2-832d3ed45bc9c87aace7f6c9b7b54065" data-private-watermark-src="v2-268829dd6407b1997945fe131d483942" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p data-pid="4XziVgmJ"&gt;Estimate:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pic3.zhimg.com/v2-5a25fed3d8482bc36374fd23809a5f77_720w.jpg?rss" data-rawwidth="781" data-rawheight="803" data-size="normal" data-caption="" data-watermark="watermark" data-original-src="v2-5a25fed3d8482bc36374fd23809a5f77" data-watermark-src="v2-e2ebe69e1b618f2f4c70794d2a2da4b1" data-private-watermark-src="v2-fe25c088fe93ed27f7a3036d9ed7026c" style="max-width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;p data-pid="eTXt95sF"&gt;References:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li data-pid="3jicorff"&gt;&lt;a href="//link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D2970694" class=" wrap external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;The Micro-Price: A High Frequency Estimator of Future Prices&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-pid="1sC0gTke"&gt;&lt;a href="//link.zhihu.com/?target=https%3A//github.com/sstoikov/microprice" class=" wrap external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;GitHub - sstoikov/microprice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;
